FBIS3-6389 "dreas052_h_94001" FBIS-EAS-94-052 Document Type:Daily Report 17 Mar 1994 Brunei, Malaysia & Singapore Malaysia Sabah Chief Minister Announces Resignation BK1703083494 Kuala Lumpur Voice of Malaysia in English 0800 GMT 17 Mar 94 BK1703083494 Kuala Lumpur Voice of Malaysia Language: English Article Type:BFN [Text] Datuk Joseph Pairin Kitingan today resigned as Sabah chief minister, a post he has held since 1985. Pairin -- who is also president of the Sabah United Party, PBS -- handed his letter of resignation personally to the governor, Tun Mohamed Said Keruak, at 1.50 pm [0550 GMT] at the Palace in Kota Kinabalu.
